targets.rawSql: SELECT username, AVG(time_ms) FROM measurement_insights GROUP BY username ORDER BY AVG(time_ms) DESC

SELECT
  username,
  COUNT(DISTINCT ROW(auth_method_name, action, visitor_id)) AS unique_count
FROM
  measurement_insights
WHERE
  NOT (action = 'signup' AND os IN ('Android', 'iOS'))
GROUP BY
  username
ORDER BY
  unique_count DESC;

SELECT 
    encounter_frequency,
    COUNT(user_id) AS "Encounter Frequency"
FROM public.users
GROUP BY 
    encounter_frequency
ORDER BY 
    "Encounter Frequency" ASC;

SELECT 
    encounter_frequency,
    AVG(auth_count_per_user) AS avg_auth_count_per_user
FROM (
    SELECT 
        u.user_id,
        u.encounter_frequency,
        COUNT(m.id) AS auth_count_per_user  -- Count of completed auth methods per user
    FROM 
        public.users AS u
    JOIN 
        public.devices AS d ON u.user_id = d.user_id
    JOIN 
        public.measurements AS m ON d.device_id = m.device_id
    GROUP BY 
        u.user_id, u.encounter_frequency
) AS user_auth_counts
GROUP BY 
    encounter_frequency
ORDER BY 
    avg_auth_count_per_user ASC;

    u.encounter_frequency

targets.rawSql:
SELECT 
    user_auth_time.age,
    AVG(user_auth_time.time_ms) AS avg_auth_count_per_age
FROM (
    SELECT 
        u.user_id,
        u.age,
        AVG(m.time_ms) AS time_ms  -- Average of required time per user
    FROM 
        public.users AS u
    JOIN 
        public.devices AS d ON u.user_id = d.user_id
    JOIN 
        public.measurements AS m ON d.device_id = m.device_id
    GROUP BY 
        u.user_id, u.age
) AS user_auth_time
GROUP BY 
    user_auth_time.age
ORDER BY 
    user_auth_time.age;

SELECT 
    auth_method_name,
    AVG(CASE WHEN action = 'signup' THEN pct_mean_stddev END) AS signup_percentage_mean_stddev,
    AVG(CASE WHEN action = 'login' THEN pct_mean_stddev END) AS login_percentage_mean_stddev
FROM (
    SELECT 
        auth_method_name,
        action,
        (STDDEV(time_ms) / AVG(time_ms)) * 100 AS pct_mean_stddev
    FROM 
        public.measurements
    GROUP BY 
        auth_method_name, action
) AS subquery
GROUP BY 
    auth_method_name
ORDER BY 
    auth_method_name;

SELECT 
    auth_method_name,
    AVG(CASE WHEN action = 'signup' THEN pct_mean_stddev END) AS signup_percentage_mean_stddev,
    AVG(CASE WHEN action = 'login' THEN pct_mean_stddev END) AS login_percentage_mean_stddev
FROM (
    SELECT 
        auth_method_name,
        action,
        STDDEV(time_ms) AS pct_mean_stddev
    FROM 
        public.measurements
    GROUP BY 
        auth_method_name, action
) AS subquery
GROUP BY 
    auth_method_name
ORDER BY 
    auth_method_name;

targets.rawSql:
WITH counts AS (
  SELECT
    m.auth_method_name,
    COUNT(CASE WHEN m.age < 30 THEN m.time_ms END) AS age_30_count
  FROM
    public.all_data AS m
  GROUP BY
    m.auth_method_name
)
SELECT
  auth_method_name,
  age_30_count::FLOAT / MAX(age_30_count) OVER () AS "< 30 years"
FROM
  counts
ORDER BY
  auth_method_name ASC;

WITH counts AS (
  SELECT
    m.auth_method_name,
    COUNT(CASE WHEN m.age > 50 THEN m.time_ms END) AS age_50_count
  FROM
    public.all_data AS m
  GROUP BY
    m.auth_method_name
)
SELECT
  auth_method_name,
  age_50_count::FLOAT / MAX(age_50_count) OVER () AS "> 50 years"
FROM
  counts
ORDER BY
  auth_method_name ASC;

targets.rawSql: SELECT auth_method_name, AVG(time_ms) AS "Average time per authentication method" FROM measurement_insights WHERE (action = 'login' OR action = 'signup') GROUP BY auth_method_name ORDER BY auth_method_name ASC

SELECT
  auth_method_name,
  COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN action = 'signup' THEN username END) AS "Signup count",
  COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN action = 'login' AND os = 'Windows' OR os = 'Mac OS' OR os = 'Linux' THEN username END) AS "Login count",
  -- COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN action = 'login' AND os <> 'Windows' AND os <> 'Mac OS' AND os <> 'Linux'  THEN username END) AS "Mobile signup count",
  COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN action = 'login' AND os <> 'Windows' AND os <> 'Mac OS' AND os <> 'Linux'  THEN username END) AS "Mobile login count"
FROM
  measurement_insights
WHERE auth_method_name != 'Device Register'
GROUP BY
  auth_method_name
ORDER BY
  auth_method_name ASC;

SELECT
  auth_method_name,
  COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN action = 'signup'AND os = 'Windows' OR os = 'Mac OS' OR os = 'Linux' THEN username END) +
  COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN action = 'login' AND os = 'Windows' OR os = 'Mac OS' OR os = 'Linux' THEN username END) +
  COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN action = 'login' AND os <> 'Windows' AND os <> 'Mac OS' AND os <> 'Linux' THEN username END) AS "Total successful auth"
FROM
  measurement_insights
WHERE auth_method_name != 'Device Register'
GROUP BY
  auth_method_name
ORDER BY
  auth_method_name ASC;

SELECT
  auth_method_name,
  COUNT(time_ms) AS "Total successful auth"
FROM
  measurement_insights
GROUP BY
  auth_method_name
ORDER BY
  auth_method_name ASC;

  COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN action = 'signup' THEN time_ms END) AS "Signup"
FROM
  measurement_insights
GROUP BY
  auth_method_name
ORDER BY
  auth_method_name ASC;

SELECT
  auth_method_name,
  AVG(CASE WHEN action = 'signup' THEN time_ms END) AS "Signup time",
  AVG(CASE WHEN action = 'login' THEN time_ms END) AS "Login time"
FROM
  measurement_insights
WHERE auth_method_name != 'Device Register'
GROUP BY
  auth_method_name
ORDER BY
  auth_method_name ASC;

SELECT
